{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":826,"text":"I want to talk to you about my kids."},{"time":3743,"text":"Now, I know everyone thinks\nthat their kid is the most fantastic,"},{"time":8415,"text":"the most beautiful kid that ever lived."},{"time":11352,"text":"But mine really are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12625,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":13956,"text":"I have 696 kids,"},{"time":16354,"text":"and they are the most intelligent,\ninventive, innovative,"},{"time":20830,"text":"brilliant and powerful kids\nthat you'll ever meet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25263,"text":"Any student I've had the honor of teaching\nin my classroom is my kid."},{"time":30702,"text":"However, because their \"real\"\nparents aren't rich"},{"time":34545,"text":"and, I argue, because they\nare mostly of color,"},{"time":37445,"text":"they will seldom get to see in themselves"},{"time":39975,"text":"the awesomeness that I see in them."},{"time":42839,"text":"Because what I see in them is myself --"},{"time":45896,"text":"or what would have been myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49645,"text":"I am the daughter of two hardworking,"},{"time":52062,"text":"college-educated, African-American parents"},{"time":54704,"text":"who chose careers as public servants:"},{"time":57442,"text":"my father, a minister;\nmy mother, an educator."},{"time":61078,"text":"Wealth was never the primary\nambition in our house."},{"time":64981,"text":"Because of this lack of wealth,"},{"time":66761,"text":"we lived in a neighborhood\nthat lacked wealth,"},{"time":68995,"text":"and henceforth a school system\nthat lacked wealth."},{"time":72307,"text":"Luckily, however, we struck\nthe educational jackpot"},{"time":76171,"text":"in a voluntary desegregation program"},{"time":78566,"text":"that buses inner-city kids --\nblack and brown --"},{"time":81958,"text":"out to suburban schools -- rich and white."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85288,"text":"At five years old, I had to take\nan hour-long bus ride"},{"time":89073,"text":"to a faraway place"},{"time":91158,"text":"to get a better education."},{"time":93522,"text":"At five years old, I thought\neveryone had a life just like mine."},{"time":98621,"text":"I thought everyone went to school"},{"time":100675,"text":"and were the only ones\nusing the brown crayons"},{"time":103058,"text":"to color in their family portraits,"},{"time":104750,"text":"while everyone else was using\nthe peach-colored ones."},{"time":108559,"text":"At five years old, I thought\neveryone was just like me."},{"time":112792,"text":"But as I got older, I started\nnoticing things, like:"},{"time":116948,"text":"How come my neighborhood friend\ndon't have to wake up"},{"time":119534,"text":"at five o'clock in the morning,"},{"time":121096,"text":"and go to a school that's an hour away?"},{"time":124278,"text":"How come I'm learning to play the violin"},{"time":126552,"text":"while my neighborhood friends\ndon't even have a music class?"},{"time":131040,"text":"Why were my neighborhood friends\nlearning and reading material"},{"time":134608,"text":"that I had done two to three years prior?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":137882,"text":"See, as I got older,"},{"time":140762,"text":"I started to have\nthis unlawful feeling in my belly,"},{"time":144715,"text":"like I was doing something\nthat I wasn't supposed to be doing;"},{"time":148647,"text":"taking something that wasn't mine;"},{"time":151819,"text":"receiving a gift,"},{"time":153544,"text":"but with someone else's name on it."},{"time":155929,"text":"All these amazing things\nthat I was being exposed to"},{"time":159457,"text":"and experiencing,"},{"time":161179,"text":"I felt I wasn't really supposed to have."},{"time":165189,"text":"I wasn't supposed to have a library,\nfully equipped athletic facilities,"},{"time":169240,"text":"or safe fields to play in."},{"time":172208,"text":"I wasn't supposed to have\ntheatre departments"},{"time":174479,"text":"with seasonal plays and concerts --"},{"time":176868,"text":"digital, visual, performing arts."},{"time":179603,"text":"I wasn't supposed to have\nfully resourced biology or chemistry labs,"},{"time":184283,"text":"school buses that brought me door-to-door,"},{"time":187109,"text":"freshly prepared school lunches"},{"time":189561,"text":"or even air conditioning."},{"time":192127,"text":"These are things my kids don't get."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194661,"text":"You see, as I got older,"},{"time":196222,"text":"while I was grateful\nfor this amazing opportunity"},{"time":199263,"text":"that I was being given,"},{"time":200933,"text":"there was this ever-present pang of:"},{"time":204210,"text":"But what about everyone else?"},{"time":207137,"text":"There are thousands\nof other kids just like me,"},{"time":210531,"text":"who deserve this, too."},{"time":212291,"text":"Why doesn't everyone get this?"},{"time":214453,"text":"Why is a high-quality education\nonly exclusive to the rich?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":219634,"text":"It was like I had some sort\nof survivor's remorse."},{"time":223222,"text":"All of my neighborhood friends\nwere experiencing"},{"time":225978,"text":"an educational train wreck"},{"time":227827,"text":"that I was saved from through a bus ride."},{"time":232067,"text":"I was like an educational Moses screaming,"},{"time":234585,"text":"\"Let my people go ..."},{"time":236218,"text":"to high-quality schools!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":238079,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":239520,"text":"I'd seen firsthand how the other half\nwas being treated and educated."},{"time":244104,"text":"I'd seen the educational promised land,"},{"time":247067,"text":"and I could not for the life of me\njustify the disparity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253550,"text":"I now teach in the very same school system\nfrom which I sought refuge."},{"time":258870,"text":"I know firsthand the tools\nthat were given to me as a student,"},{"time":263431,"text":"and now as a teacher, I don't have\naccess to those same tools"},{"time":267378,"text":"to give my students."},{"time":269451,"text":"There have been countless nights\nwhen I've cried in frustration,"},{"time":274050,"text":"anger"},{"time":275350,"text":"and sorrow,"},{"time":276765,"text":"because I can't teach my kids\nthe way that I was taught,"},{"time":280581,"text":"because I don't have access\nto the same resources or tools"},{"time":284796,"text":"that were used to teach me."},{"time":287393,"text":"My kids deserve so much better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290270,"text":"We sit and we keep banging\nour heads against this term:"},{"time":293157,"text":"\"Achievement gap, achievement gap!\""},{"time":296462,"text":"Is it really that hard to understand"},{"time":299418,"text":"why these kids perform well\nand these kids don't?"},{"time":302667,"text":"I mean, really."},{"time":304664,"text":"I think we've got it all wrong."},{"time":306955,"text":"I think we,"},{"time":308140,"text":"as Gloria Ladson-Billings says,"},{"time":310246,"text":"should flip our paradigm and our language\nand call it what it really is."},{"time":315516,"text":"It's not an achievement gap;"},{"time":317878,"text":"it's an education debt,"},{"time":320417,"text":"for all of the foregone schooling\nresources that were never invested"},{"time":325719,"text":"in the education of the black\nand brown child over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330820,"text":"A little-known secret in American history"},{"time":333870,"text":"is that the only American institution\ncreated specifically for people of color"},{"time":339714,"text":"is the American slave trade --"},{"time":341866,"text":"and some would argue the prison system,"},{"time":343839,"text":"but that's another topic\nfor another TED Talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346089,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":347654,"text":"The public school system of this country\nwas built, bought and paid for"},{"time":351971,"text":"using commerce generated\nfrom the slave trade and slave labor."},{"time":356651,"text":"While African-Americans were enslaved\nand prohibited from schooling,"},{"time":360638,"text":"their labor established\nthe very institution"},{"time":363821,"text":"from which they were excluded."},{"time":366042,"text":"Ever since then, every court case,\neducational policy, reform,"},{"time":371145,"text":"has been an attempt\nto retrofit the design,"},{"time":374423,"text":"rather than just stopping\nand acknowledging:"},{"time":377107,"text":"we've had it all wrong from the beginning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381243,"text":"An oversimplification\nof American educational history."},{"time":385310,"text":"All right, just bear with me."},{"time":387681,"text":"Blacks were kept out -- you know,\nthe whole slavery thing."},{"time":391256,"text":"With the help\nof philanthropic white people,"},{"time":393357,"text":"they built their own schools."},{"time":394935,"text":"Separate but equal was OK."},{"time":397729,"text":"But while we all know\nthings were indeed separate,"},{"time":400483,"text":"they were in no ways equal."},{"time":402571,"text":"Enter Brown v. the Board of Education\nof Topeka, Kansas in 1954;"},{"time":407760,"text":"legal separation of the races\nis now illegal."},{"time":411900,"text":"But very few people pay attention\nto all of the court cases since then,"},{"time":418153,"text":"that have undone the educational\npromised land for every child"},{"time":423450,"text":"that Brown v. Board intended."},{"time":426438,"text":"Some argue that today our schools\nare now more segregated"},{"time":430180,"text":"than they ever were before we tried\nto desegregate them in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435963,"text":"Teaching my kids about desegregation,\nthe Little Rock Nine,"},{"time":439580,"text":"the Civil Rights Movement,"},{"time":440907,"text":"is a real awkward moment in my classroom,"},{"time":444261,"text":"when I have to hear\nthe voice of a child ask,"},{"time":447940,"text":"\"If schools were desegregated in 1954,"},{"time":451267,"text":"how come there are no white kids here?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":453588,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":455072,"text":"These kids aren't dumb."},{"time":457292,"text":"They know exactly what's happening,"},{"time":459542,"text":"and what's not."},{"time":461526,"text":"They know that when it comes to schooling,"},{"time":464670,"text":"black lives don't matter"},{"time":467081,"text":"and they never have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470316,"text":"For years, I tried desperately\nto cultivate in my kids a love of reading."},{"time":477416,"text":"I'd amassed a modest classroom library"},{"time":480304,"text":"of books I'd accumulated\nfrom secondhand shops,"},{"time":483625,"text":"thrift stores, attics -- you know."},{"time":486112,"text":"But whenever I said those dreadful words,"},{"time":488596,"text":"\"Take out a book and read,\""},{"time":490816,"text":"you'd think I'd just declared war."},{"time":493273,"text":"It was torture."},{"time":495693,"text":"One day,"},{"time":497184,"text":"after I'd heard about this website\ncalled DonorsChoose,"},{"time":500338,"text":"where classroom teachers create wish lists"},{"time":502678,"text":"of items they need for their classroom"},{"time":504806,"text":"and anonymous donors fulfill them,"},{"time":507357,"text":"I figured I'd go out on a limb\nand just make a wish list"},{"time":511382,"text":"of the teenager's dream library."},{"time":515698,"text":"Over 200 brand-new books\nwere sent to my room piece by piece."},{"time":520672,"text":"Every day there were new deliveries\nand my kids would exclaim with glee,"},{"time":525269,"text":"\"This feels like Christmas!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":527250,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":528354,"text":"Then they'd say,"},{"time":529543,"text":"\"Ms. Sumner, where did\nthese books come from?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":532439,"text":"And then I'd reply,"},{"time":533679,"text":"\"Strangers from all over the country\nwanted you to have these.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":538274,"text":"And then they'd say, almost suspiciously,"},{"time":542474,"text":"\"But they're brand-new.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":544225,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":545251,"text":"To which I'd reply,"},{"time":546854,"text":"\"You deserve brand-new books.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":550137,"text":"The whole experience hit home\nfor me when one of my girls,"},{"time":553584,"text":"as she peeled open a crisp paperback said,"},{"time":557582,"text":"\"Ms. Sumner -- you know,\nI figured you bought these books,"},{"time":561984,"text":"'cause you teachers\nare always buying us stuff."},{"time":565158,"text":"But to know that a stranger,\nsomeone I don't even know,"},{"time":569211,"text":"cares this much about me"},{"time":571480,"text":"is pretty cool.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":573870,"text":"Knowing that strangers\nwill take care of you"},{"time":576519,"text":"is a privilege my kids aren't afforded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580342,"text":"Ever since the donation,"},{"time":581808,"text":"there has been a steady stream of kids\nsigning out books to take home,"},{"time":585690,"text":"and then returning them\nwith the exclamation,"},{"time":588374,"text":"\"This one was good!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":589986,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":591058,"text":"Now when I say,\n\"Take out a book and read,\""},{"time":593384,"text":"kids rush to my library."},{"time":596849,"text":"It wasn't that they didn't want to read,"},{"time":598920,"text":"but instead, they'd gladly read\nif the resources were there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605579,"text":"Institutionally speaking,"},{"time":607255,"text":"our public school system has never\ndone right by the black and brown child."},{"time":612068,"text":"We keep focusing on the end results"},{"time":614640,"text":"or test results,"},{"time":616029,"text":"and getting frustrated."},{"time":617899,"text":"We get to a catastrophe and we wonder,"},{"time":620060,"text":"\"How did it get so bad?\nHow did we get here?\""},{"time":623890,"text":"Really?"},{"time":625439,"text":"If you neglect a child long enough,"},{"time":627538,"text":"you no longer have\nthe right to be surprised"},{"time":630652,"text":"when things don't turn out well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633319,"text":"Stop being perplexed"},{"time":635077,"text":"or confused"},{"time":636727,"text":"or befuddled"},{"time":638680,"text":"by the achievement gap,"},{"time":640630,"text":"the income gap,"},{"time":641877,"text":"the incarceration rates,"},{"time":643520,"text":"or whatever socioeconomic disparity\nis the new \"it\" term for the moment."},{"time":649248,"text":"The problems we have as a country"},{"time":651714,"text":"are the problems we created as a country."},{"time":654740,"text":"The quality of your education\nis directly proportionate"},{"time":658302,"text":"to your access to college,"},{"time":660184,"text":"your access to jobs,"},{"time":661936,"text":"your access to the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665594,"text":"Until we live in a world where every kid\ncan get a high-quality education"},{"time":670888,"text":"no matter where they live,"},{"time":672448,"text":"or the color of their skin,"},{"time":674352,"text":"there are things we can do\non a macro level."},{"time":679389,"text":"School funding should not\nbe decided by property taxes"},{"time":682977,"text":"or some funky economic equation"},{"time":685232,"text":"where rich kids continue\nto benefit from state aid,"},{"time":688292,"text":"while poor kids are continuously\nhaving food and resources"},{"time":692401,"text":"taken from their mouths."},{"time":694750,"text":"Governors, senators, mayors,\ncity council members --"},{"time":698535,"text":"if we're going to call\npublic education public education,"},{"time":701423,"text":"then it should be just that."},{"time":703555,"text":"Otherwise, we should\ncall it what it really is:"},{"time":706562,"text":"poverty insurance."},{"time":709211,"text":"\"Public education:"},{"time":710677,"text":"keeping poor kids poor since 1954.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":713789,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":716733,"text":"If we really, as a country, believe\nthat education is the \"great equalizer,\""},{"time":721855,"text":"then it should be just that:\nequal and equitable."},{"time":726158,"text":"Until then, there's no democracy\nin our democratic education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731493,"text":"On a mezzo level:"},{"time":733640,"text":"historically speaking, the education\nof the black and brown child"},{"time":736866,"text":"has always depended\non the philanthropy of others."},{"time":740361,"text":"And unfortunately, today it still does."},{"time":743770,"text":"If your son or daughter or niece\nor nephew or neighbor"},{"time":748159,"text":"or little Timmy down the street"},{"time":750253,"text":"goes to an affluent school,"},{"time":752580,"text":"challenge your school committee\nto adopt an impoverished school"},{"time":755778,"text":"or an impoverished classroom."},{"time":757841,"text":"Close the divide by engaging\nin communication"},{"time":761262,"text":"and relationships that matter."},{"time":764050,"text":"When resources are shared,"},{"time":766028,"text":"they're not divided;"},{"time":767744,"text":"they're multiplied."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769871,"text":"And on a micro level:"},{"time":771734,"text":"if you're a human being,"},{"time":773985,"text":"donate."},{"time":775524,"text":"Time, money, resources, opportunities --"},{"time":779611,"text":"whatever is in your heart."},{"time":782847,"text":"There are websites like DonorsChoose"},{"time":785075,"text":"that recognize the disparity"},{"time":787153,"text":"and actually want\nto do something about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791748,"text":"What is a carpenter with no tools?"},{"time":794350,"text":"What is an actress with no stage?"},{"time":796990,"text":"What is a scientist with no laboratory?"},{"time":799859,"text":"What is a doctor with no equipment?"},{"time":803270,"text":"I'll tell you:"},{"time":804970,"text":"they're my kids."},{"time":807219,"text":"Shouldn't they be your kids, too?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":809893,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811068,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}